In a small #pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 3/4 cup water, @turmeric{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce. Trim and finely dice @mini cucumber{1}(finely diced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}(chopped).

In a small #bowl{}, combine cucumber, @sour cream{3%tbsp}, @yogurt{4%tbsp}, half the @garlic powder{2%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge, and a pinch of dill. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Juice from two lemon wedges and a large pinch of dill for 4 servings.

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

> For seamless timing, start chicken when rice has 10 minutes remaining!

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; season with @dried oregano{1%tsp}, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-40%seconds}. Cut into quarters.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide rice, chicken, and pitas between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Serve with tzatziki and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.